content.detailedDescription:
As noted above, this sighting occurred on the clear night of tuesday 21st july 2015. i had just finished a late walk, with my dog in a forested area north of where i live. slowly walking back on the gravel road (walking north) looking up at stars i stopped & turned around to look at the southern sky. at exactly 10:05 pm i witnessed a very bright star like ufo appear in the sky. (brighter that all other stars). it started ascending slowly in an erratic manner (moving side to side), with the brightness of the object changing as it went (bright white). (pulsating). a few seconds later (~15-20 seconds) another bright star like ufo appeared, from the same spot in the sky as the first. the second also started acting in a similar manner, ascending, erratic movement, pulsating brightness. not even ~5-10 seconds later a third bright star like ufo appeared, again from the same spot in the sky & started behaving like the other two. i witnessed all three star like ufo's ascend upwards in the manner described above, for a couple minutes (~2 min). then all three ufo's became stationary in the sky (at the same time), & stabilized their brightness. at this point all three looked like stars. (same brightness as the other stars). although the first ufo that appeared was notably brighter, than the other two that were stationary below it in the sky.        


(i initially thought (for the first 5 seconds) when observing the first ufo appear in the sky, that it was a commercial plane (with head lights on) that had turned toward me in the sky. but quickly realized, after witnessing it erratic movements that i was incorrect. needless to say this was affirmed after observing the other two ufo's appear from nowhere & perform the same movement/ pulsating actions.


after all three ufo's became stationary in the southern sky i decided to pull out my phone & take a picture (10:08 pm). (i was in awe when this was happening & taking a picture or video didn't even cross my mind)! i snapped a photo & 30 second video (which i have) but both didn't turn out.. just black, no stars or anything). quickly realizing my attempts of documentation we're useless, i decided to signal to them...

i flashed my phone (i phone 5) flashlight at these now stationary ufo's twice & watched. not even a minute later (~30-45 seconds), i observed a fourth ufo appear in the southern sky from the same spot as the others. this one displayed the same movements & pulsating characteristics as the others. but this one flew almost right over me (slightly to my right, in the south western sky) & the most amazing thing proceeded to happen... 

this fourth star like (round) ufo was much closer than the other three (within 1km, although it is hard to estimate). when it got almost right over me changed into an oval shape & flashed the brightest white light at me twice!! then disappeared!!!! ... i have no words to describe ... 

my feelings we're that of goose bumps, awe, humbleness, warmth, friendship & love.. very strange, i find it hard to describe in words.

i was brought to tears, which i can tell you doesn't happen often..

anyways, i sat & watched the three stationary ufo's for almost two hours (until 11:45 pm), did not observe any other movements in them / or change in color.  nothing else unusual was observed in that time so i got in my car & went home, because i had work in the morning. 


i would just like to note this is the first time i have reported a sighting / experience. thank you for all your efforts!


most sincerely, 


john
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Witnessed three bright star like ufo's appear from the same spot in the sky, 'dance' then become stationary. flashed my phone flashlight at these things twice & observed a fourth ufo appear. it proceeded to flash the brightest white light at me twice!

content.detailedDescription: I was driving down david drive in metairie, louisiana and i saw to my right, above the houses and trees several (6 - 9) of these small, white, geometrically shaped ufos (possibly dodecahedrons, about two or three times as big as a soccer ball) flying along at a seemingly casual, slow pace, possibly a pace slow enough to allow them to observe the land and sites below them.  i was surprised to see that none of the other drivers around me seemed to notice the ufos. the ufos did not seem to be glowing or have lights, but they were seemingly silent and the material they were made of was reminiscent of the white material that things like the ship from star trek, star wars, and others, this white material that ships from those shows/movies are made of.  i would note that these things did not seem scary to me and that these ufos, in some weird way, seemed like they were a bunch of friends flying along to just check out the area.  they were flying in a direction that put them on a path where they gradually got further and further away from me and i lost sight of them. also, this was a very long time ago, but i hoped that maybe someone else saw similar ufos either around that time (1992 or so) or since then and maybe had something to share about them.
content.summary: Small, white geometric shaped (dodecahedrons) about twice the size of soccer balls flying above houses and trees.

content.detailedDescription: I must have been around 7 or 8 (around 1974)? i was walking to a friends house when all of a sudden i had the sensation that someone was looking at me? i turned around a saw some shiny lights hovering above the treeline that was to the right and rear of my house. at first, i was confused thinking it was a helicopter? then i realized that in fact it was several orbs. they were several different colors, all shiny like christmas tree decorations. a sense of calm came over me, then i heard a voice that was neither masculine nor feminine. telepathically it spoke to me and said,"we will always be watching over you." i nodded my head, as to say "yes i understand." and then the orbs slowly moved to my left, which would be to the east. at this point, i turned around and continued on to my friends house. i don't remember this "encounter" affecting that day? later i would be able to remember that day. this memory is around 40 years old and yet, i remember it as it was yesterday. thank you for allowing me to share this with you.
content.summary: Observed "orbs" above treeline.

content.detailedDescription:
My family and i were driving back from florida on the evening of june 17th 2015. we first observed the objects as we neared phenix city, to the ne over the treeline. this was on us hwy 431 headed north. we had not made it to the city yet (still very dark along highway) and we observed this cluster. the most notable characteristic was that is was very bright. i thought maybe they were military signal flares over fort benning, but they did not seem to move or dissipate.

i lost sight of them due to the city and obstructions until later. after about 20 minutes, we crossed over into ga on us hwy 80, stopping at bradley park exit for something to eat prior to getting on i-185. it was approximately 10pm est, and i snapped 3 photos with my cellphone prior to going into the restaurant. after we ate (about 1/2 hour) we left, and i did not see the objects in the sky anymore.

the pictures i took were roughly se of our location (over columbus), in the direction we had traveled from when we first observed them. i estimate they were a few miles away, as we had observed them from southern and northern vantage points that were 20 minutes travel time by car apart.
content.summary: Very bright cluster over columbus ga / phenix city al area

content.detailedDescription: I was at a party and we were outside and i saw a quick flash of light in the corner of my eye so i looked up to see what it was.  i see a light, almost directly overhead towards the west, that looks like a really large star starting to change into all visible colors, one at a time.  i had no idea what i was looking at and the only things that i could justify claiming that it was had to be either lightning, a shooting star or a firework since it was only a few weeks after july 4, but a split second after i discovered the object, it shot off in a straight line to the east leaving a trail of light that was changing colors as well.  though i could not tell the size or altitude, it was obvious that the object was traveling faster than any plane or aircraft i have even experienced,   it was apparent that the object was separated from the trail even though the colors changed in the trail it left.  almost immediately after this happened, the light and its trail of light disappeared.  i felt like the object knew that i had spotted it and therefore took off as quickly as it could.  i also considered that it was phasing in and out of high speed travel.  as mentioned before, it was hard to determine the altitude, but it was too high to be a firework and i feel that it's fair to say it wasn't lightning because of the nature of its beeline flight path.  this leaves the possibility of a shooting star, but it too large in my opinion and i was in an urban area that caused enough light pollution that you had a hard time making out the brightest stars. i have seen shooting stars before, but it didn't feel the same and the object did fly in a straight line, i have yet to see a shooting star that doesn't have some curve in it's flight path.  there wasn't any sound coming from the object or afterwards which helps to debunk the possibility of it being a firework or lightning   to my dismay, i discovered that i was the only one that saw the object at the party.
content.summary: Quick flash of light, cycling of colored lights and quickly flew away

content.detailedDescription:
On the morning of 22/07/2015, i was beach fishing on stokes bay beach gosport hampshire uk, i noticed a light high in the sky moving in a north easterly direction. my initial thought maybe satelite, or possibly the international space station.

  after a few moments the light brightened, i looked for aircraft navigation lights, there were none. the light seemed to fall from the sky, a moment later a huge pulsing pure white `not a reflective light`, it looked like a
"blob" or a "splat" was above me i had felt a pressure change i remember taking an intake of breath, i was fixed to the spot trying to take in what i was witnessing,then a large orb slowly ejected from the object accended vertically above getting smaller to its zenith and started dancing about high in the sky. i noticed a very pale yellow haze around me, moments later the main object started to dim, until this moment i did not see a solid craft what i did see was, what i thought looked like the top of the eifel tower,a solid airial perhaps, definatley solid and looked metallic.
 the main object blinked out, the small orb was still high in the sky, i saw another light i believe was the main object connect to the the small orb then move off to the north east for a few seconds then blinked out.

  the night of the 22/07/2015, was clear starlit, no cloud.

  during the sighting i felt totally calm, even recall a smile on my face,i do recall being fixed to the spot my arms down by my side no fear totally calm however when sighting was over, i felt vunerable an fearfull, i looked at my watch it was 0210, i felt i had to get away i packed my gear and left.

  i had been on the beach for around 30 minutes before, and was wearing a beach light on my head, i wear glasses, looked above my glasses frame to confirm there was no reflection of head light.
content.summary: Night fishing large moving white light above, orb ejected danced high in sky joined together with main light

content.detailedDescription:
In 1965 my friend and i were living in calgary alberta. we had just come from red lake ontario. i was 18 at the time . my friend rick was 16. one evening we went to the calgary drive in movie lot at dusk.  the cartoons came up first on the screen. we were in my car watching them.Just as the main movie was starting it suddenly got very bright out side. there was a brilliant light above us so bright that the gravel in the lot looked white.Rick said i did not see flood lights above this place. people were honking their car horns in protest.
the lot was full of teen age kids most had dates. two small four foot grey beings came to our car.I heard in my head that one was asking me questions. there was no sound from it. it s small lips did not move. it said you are both male. why do you not have females with you?  do you mate with each outher.  i replied we are not from here. we are hoping to find females. we come from ontario. we were taken somehow to an inspection area and placed on a table. there were lots of tables there with teens on them. we were examined by much taller 5 or 6 foot greys with almond shaped eyes and big heads.    the next thing i knew we were back in my car and the sun was comming up. it was saturday morning. rick asked what happened to us? i told him stay here i am going to the confectionary to ask outher kids questions.
  one girl was freeking out  there were lots of guys and girls. there was total confusion there.   she was saying he was doing things to me. personal private things. her boyfriend was a big guy that was really angry.He asked her who did was it that guy and pointed at me.   i left as i did not want trouble from him. i went back to my car. rick asked what do you know. i told rick all i know for sure is that it is morning the sun is comming up and we missed the movie so lets go home. when i undressed for bed i noticed a small quarter inch egg shaped mark on my inner thigh. it was light brown. it did not hurt. i still have it there to this day. i am now a senior citisen and have often wondered what took place that night
content.summary: We communicated with something and were examined

content.detailedDescription: I was outside of my house having a smoke with a cousin, when i noticed an odd light from the corner of my eye. we watched as it flew from the southern part of our town, to farther than the eye can see north, beyond the tree line. as we witness this add object fly, it was dipping and seeming like it was dropping hundreds of feet in a moment, then it would turn and abruptly be back up and back on course as if it never fell, it would swerve from side to side and change path going from east to west while continuing to head north. 5-6 shooting stars were seen during this time, and shortly after. two-three minutes after, we saw a similar object, coming from the northern part of our sight going south, except this time it was on east side of town. similar characteristics as the first time. me and my cousin watched as they flew by silently, and traceless. we went inside for a few minutes to get more smokes, when we went outside, we shortly after saw the exact same thing once again. coming from the south side of town, on the west side, going north, then returning from the north, on the east side of town. i noticed the object because of the flashing lights on it, and its un-normal flying pattern. we were not sure what we were witnessing at first, if it was military or not, (are area does not have a base near it, and very rarely see any form of military aircraft passing over town, and if we do, its big, loud, leaves some trails; and during the day) we know its not a commercial air line, because of the flight trajectory wouldn't make sense, and those passengers wouldn't be very happy being tossed around side to side, and dropping hundreds of feet suddenly then quickly raised higher than initially. we were kinda shocked about what we saw, but were kinda accepting of what we saw, this isn't our first sightings in this area. fraserdale highway has lots of sightings. we always lost sight of the object due to it going out of our sight vision (going to far)
content.summary: Views 4 objects fly from s to north, short time period then north to south. then repeated once again

content.detailedDescription: I was in central ohio.  it was around 1am, and i just arrived home from work.  i was letting my three dogs outside to relieve themselves.  i leaned back up against the railing of my deck, to "crack" my back and i was looking up at the sky.  i noticed a cluster of three "stars", and it seemed the middle one was slowly moving.  i looked away and rubbed my eyes.  i looked back and it was still moving, but maybe a little quicker.  it started a little north of my location, and was moving southward.  still not fast, but clearly moving away from the cluster of stars i thought it was with.  it always maintained the appearance of a star; just a glowing white light that didn't blink or change color.  after a couple of minutes of watching, i had pretty much convinced myself it was some aircraft flying at high altitude, with no blinking lights that i could see.  then it suddenly started to wobble from side to side like it was negotiating a curvy mountain road.  the speed never seemed to appreciably change, and it kept up the side to side meandering as it disappeared out of view toward the south past the rooftops and tree line south of my location.  the total time i was able to view it was at least 5 minutes, but no more than 10 minutes.  i kept hoping it would speed up and "zip" away at a high rate of speed thereby making me feel like i had seen something truly special, but its rate of speed seemed very constant.  the aspect that made me doubt i was seeing some kind of man-made, conventional craft was the odd wobble or side to side motion that it made.  at that height, i just couldn't imagine that it was a helicopter or other conventional craft making that maneuver at that perceived altitude.  nor could i imagine why a craft would be making that type of maneuver at all.  that makes it a ufo to me.
content.summary: I witnessed what i first thought were three stars, then i noticed the middle of the three was moving slowly across the sky from north to south, after following a straight line for a couple minutes, it started wobbling until i couldn't see it any longer

content.summary: Military activity with ufo

content.detailedDescription: I was working on the roof of my house on a weekend in the summer/fall of 1999 and to the south i saw three black military looking helicopters flying north, just above the tree tops following the nearby highway 97. later that same afternoon, still working on my roof i saw one of the black helicopters return, flying low almost directly over my house, seeming to me at the time to be getting a better look at what i was doing on the roof, then after passing over my house the helicopter changed direction and flew off to the north. later that night at about 3-4 am i awoke to use the washroom. when i returned to my bedroom i saw a moving light out my bedroom window and it caught my attention. i went up to the window which faces almost due north and noticed other lights in a place in the sky i know were not stars. as i watched i noticed 2 stationary lights (i beleive to be helicopters) one at a lower altitude and the other in line at a higher altitude, and a third moving light/helicopter farther to the east. as i watched i realized that a fourth light, between the first two stationary lights and the moving light. doing the same maneuvers as the light that was moving further to the east was doing. i took note of this because the third and fourth lights never went higher(ascend) or lower (decend) than the first two stationary lights. as i watched i noticed that the fourth light was doing the same movements as the third light but at a way faster speed. i noticed that the third light moved as i know a helicopter would move, then when it finished moving the fourth light would do the same movement or pattern as the third light did but it moved unimaginably fast. the third light (which i believe to be a helicopter) would move in many different ways like ascending,descending, form a figure 8 or a z etc. never going higher or lower then the two stationary lights to the west at different altitudes. and the fourth light would mimic the movements of the moving light but it was moving at a speed and changing directions that no helicopter could ever do. i belive what i was watching was two stationary helicopters at different altitudes and a third, moving helicopter, and some kind of experimental or other worldly aircraft that was being tested. i watched these lights for 15-20 minutes and then returned to my bed to sleep. being that the event happened so long ago i do not remember the exact month or day but i'm sure it was 1999. i will remember this sighting for the rest of my life.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering,Other
content.summary: I watched a moving light/aircraft accend, decend, and do various manuvers copying an other slower moving light/aircraft and 2 stationary lights/aircraft's i believe to be a helicopters

content.detailedDescription: Myself and my late father where outside our bungalow enjoying the afternoon sunshine in around 2000 - 2001, my father had some binoculars which he used to like viewing aeroplanes passing overhead with when he noticed something to the north east direction some distance away over middlesbrough and asked me to look through the binoculars to see if i knew what it was when i looked i saw a silver cylindrical spinning object that was close to some clouds i said to my father i thought it was a ufo and ran into the house to get my old betamax video camera which i filmed the object for about 30 seconds to a minute as it  spun  on the spot then darted into cloud then back to its first spot then behind the cloud again. then my camera battery ran out but i still have the video but it's on a betamax tape and i don't have a betamax player no more.
content.summary: My father and i observed a spinning  cylindrical  diver coloured  object that darted in and out of clouds over the middlesbrough area in 2000 / 2001

the blinds of the window were not closed yet but i could see him clearly. 
i was not feeling that i was in danger  or anything so i stood there for a good 20sec. i had no clue what to do, i was in shock. and me and him/her/it just stood there staring at each other  after i ran away. not sure if i ran the room across the hall or back to wash room, or downstairs to find my parents.
 after 5 mins i went back to my room as i peeked in my room i saw that he was not there but i ran up to my window and i could see lights at the edge of the forest and in the forest behind my house. the light looked blue/white and there were blinking. not sure if the actual light was blinking or it was the fact that the lights were in the forest and it was the trees making them blink.

content.detailedDescription: Walking east on a farm road, back towards gramma's  farm we were all watching the stars. clear warm summer evening. all looking for the" north star". i will not speak for the other 6 kids. but we saw 9 bright stars in the north sky. at first they looked like stars. as we got near the house we could see that these "stars" were moving in a rotating formation. we went in the house and reported this activity to the adults. outside in the yard, i along with many others, watched a cigar shaped object seemingly float over head at 200ft alt max. not a large object, no sound, but a belt of light on its mid "belly". alt lights in a band red, blue green, yellow. as it lit up there was no sequence ,but once or twice a color would highlight. this object was moving slow enough that grampa said "i'm getting my gun". dad said no. just then we heard a very loud jet sound ,and  saw a jet, fighter type, wiz past. again very low. the cigar was gone and so were the  2 jets.  we watched the south sky for a while and we could see the bright stars in formation until they were lost in the stars. gramma had sent me an article clipping from the iowa city paper a year later saying that 2 usaf jets had chased  an un id fl ob. i would like to find out what this could have been. i have to say.... i saw i believe.
content.summary: 9 craft w to e  cigar shape belly band of alt lights slow speed until chased by usaf

content.detailedDescription: Can someone tell me if this is a ufo. ok i'm out on the patio letting the dogs out and i see this white dot in the distance. as it's getting closer i noticed it was only flying about the height of a helicopter way too low for an airplane i don't think it was a helicopter only for the fact there was no sound nothing at all. it was moving so slow almost a standstill it seemed like as it got closer i noticed it was a triangle shape almost like a perfect piece of pie with huge white lights on the bottom six or maybe seven of them as i'm staring at this thing i see another set of lights coming in the distance then another set three all together in perfect formation evenly spaced apart. i tried getting the phone of my pocket to record it but to be honest i was a little freaked out and had a little bit of a problem but i did catch the other two. the lights were really bright so my phone cannot focus because of this but if you look you can see some light turning on and off lost sight of it over the houses. there were some red lights on the bottom from the front going down the middle to the end. they flashed like a strobe light start in the front turn on one at a time all the way to the back.
content.summary: Looking at it and froze up

content.detailedDescription: Driving. i saw a huge white blimp looking thing out the window. that was my initial thought, of course. it remained hovering. it was just under the clouds, but there were only a few clouds in the sky. it was against the blue. it was completely feature less. i pointed it out to my brother. then we watched in confusion as it disappeared over the horizon at unbelievable speeds. it was almost above me and almost gone in five seconds.
content.summary: Large blimp or white zeppelin, completely colorless

content.detailedDescription: My ex-girlfriend and i were travelling to nitinat lake on the west coast of vancouver island to camp and fish.  it was late in a very secluded area and we had been drinking for a while, anyway we were naked and some silly conversation had her getting ready to pee on the fire.  i told her i was going to take pictures, these were the result.  it wasn't until we looked at the pictures on the computer when we got back a few days later that we saw the streak of light going into the motor home and hovering above my laptop.
content.summary: I took a series of 9 pictures, 4 of them have a steak of light i cannot explain.

content.detailedDescription: Please call me and i'll give you the details. life changing event.
content.summary: I believe that my brother and i had an encounter.  we just finally discussed it,18 years later
